Author-Name:  Ray, Edward John
Title:   Intraindustry Trade: 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 1278-91
Issue: 6
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  December 
Abstract:
  This paper provides an empirical analysis of the determinants of
 intraindustry trade. The authors demonstrat that two-way trade flows occur
 where conditions are favorable to international specialization consistent
 with the Stigler-Williamson analysis of the division of labor. The results
 are inconsistent wit h the prevailing product differentiation-cum-scale
 economies model of intraindustry trade. In addition, the authors show that
 intraindustr y trade has a significant impact on protectionist pressures.
 Exports of closely related products have the effect of mitigating the
 tariff- raising effects that imports would otherwise exert.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
