Title:   Treble Damage Awards in Private Lawsuits for Price Fixing. 
Journal: Journal of Political Economy
Pages: 1326-36
Issue: 6
Volume: 95
Year: 1987
Month:  December 
Abstract:
  The traditional model for assessing the effects of treble damage pena
 lties on price fixing is reexamined and shown to yield surprising res
 ults. Unless the probability of detection is extremely sensitive to the
 price charged, increasing the damage multiple will affect neither market
 efficiency nor expected distribution, and will raise the mark et price.  Copyright 1987 by University of Chicago Press.
